OL,7,F"Instead it was just brushed under the
OL,8,Fcarpet.
OL,10,F"You didn't mention that it could have
OL,11,Fbeen the fault of the medical
OL,12,Fprofession or the government."
OL,14,FA quarter of a century later and
OL,15,Fthey're still feeling the
OL,16,Fconsequences. Andrew's illness meant
OL,17,Fhuge financial struggles and
OL,18,Fsacrifices for the family.
